main event: A ground visual observation of a UFO in Cheyenne, Wyoming on 31 August 1965, consisting of one object observed for 15 minutes.
interesting points: The object was described as a ring of light that rapidly outlined before disappearing., It emitted no sound., The object exhibited red, white, blue, and green colors., The flight path of the object was noted to be westward and then eastward., The conclusion of the report stated that there was insufficient data for evaluation.
sighted object: A ring of light in the sky
witness description: Information relayed through AF Command Post; no direct witnesses confirmed.
